dct_title_s: Germany: International frontiers 1937. Internal boundaries 1944: Gaue (Nazi Party boundaries). Series G.S.G.S. Misc. no. 162
dct_description_sm: Map shows the Gaue boundaries by red lines and the headquarters are undersocore. Also, international, Länder, Provinzen, Regierungsbezirk, Kreis boundaries. Map shows the borders of the Greater Germany Reich covering: Germany, parts of Poland, and Russia. "7/Jan45/13 MRS/224". "1/Jan45/13 MRS/266". Overprinted on a map from the series GSGS Misc. 162. East Decimal Degree 22.9167. South Decimal Degree 47.2667. West Decimal Degree 5.8667. North Decimal Degree 55.166700. Map is part of a set of four sheets: Wehrkreise (Military districts); Luftgaue (Air Force districts); Gaue (Nazi Party boundaries); Wirtschaftsbezirke (Economic districts). Library has: Gaue (Nazy Party boundaries).
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section
